rosinone, Lazio, Italië","Napoli, Napoli, Campania, Italia":"Napoli, Napoli, Campania, Italië","Europe":"Europa","Roma, Lazio, Italy":"Roma, Lazio, Italië","Napoli, Napoli, Campania, Itália":"Napoli, Napoli, Campania, Italië","Roccasecca, Roma, Lazio, Italy":"Roccasecca, Roma, Lazio, Italië"},"en":{"1098–circa 1160":"1098–about 1160","1098–1160":"1098–1160","1097–1160":"1097–1160","1100–Female":"1100–Deceased","1124–Male":"1124–Deceased","1125–1157":"1125–1157","1070–1118":"1070–1118","1062–1121":"1062–1121","1121":"1121","1098":"1098","1097":"1097","1062":"1062","1160":"1160","1070":"1070","1118":"1118","1125":"1125","1125?":"1125","1157":"1157","1124":"1124","circa 1160":"about 1160","1100":"1100","AFT MAR 1118":"after March 1118","about 1124":"about 1124","Roccasecca, Frosinone, Lazio, Italia":"Roccasecca, Frosinone, Lazio, Italy","Napoli, Napoli, Campania, Italia":"Naples, Naples, Campania, Italy","Europe":"Europe","Roma, Lazio, Italy":"Roma, Lazio, Italy","Napoli, Napoli, Campania, Itália":"Naples, Naples, Campania, Italy","Roccasecca, Roma, Lazio, Italy":"Roccasecca, Roma, Lazio, Italy","nameMeanings":[{"name":"di","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Chinese:","Mandarin form of the surname 狄, a term referring to the tribes in ancient northern China: (i) from Di (狄), the name of an ancient state (thought to have been located in Hebei or Shandong province), which was granted to Xiao Bo or Kao Bo by King Cheng of Zhou (reigned 1042–1021  BC ). (ii) adopted as a surname by the Ku Di (庫狄) family during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iii) traced back to other minority ethnic groups in ancient northwestern China.","Mandarin form of the Chinese surname 邸, meaning ‘official residence’ in Chinese: (i) from placename Di (邸), the name of a county (unidentified location). (ii) said to be borne by some descendants of Kujula Kadphises (called 丘就郤 or 邸就郤 in Chinese, 30–<i>c.</i> 80  AD ), founder of the Kushan Empire (one branch of the Yuezhi people originating from western China) located in Central Asia during the Eastern Han dynasty (25–220  AD )."],"variants":[{"name":"Chi","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Young, Dong, Yun, Cheng, Jae, Yong, Cheng Chung, Chi, Chun, Duk, Fang, Feng.  Korean Chung, Chong, Jae Hong, Moon, Myong, Pong, Shen, Yoo, Byung, Chang, Chol, Chong Hun.  Southeast Asian Phi, Hung, Ly, Tu, Denh, Do Van, Duong, Hao, Kieu, Mui, Nga, Phat.","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 池, meaning ‘moat’ in ancient Chinese: (i) acquired as a surname by people who lived beside a moat. (ii) from Chi (池), said to be the name of an ancient state (of unknown location and period). (iii) from the personal name Chi (池), personal name of a son of an official in the state of Qin during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 遲, meaning ‘late’ in Chinese: (i) borne by descendants of Chi Ren (遲任), a person who lived during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). (ii) shortened form of the Chinese compound surname Yu-Chi (尉遲), originally the name of a tribe from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China. (iii) from the second element of the personal name Zi Chi (子遲), style name of Fan Xu, a student of Confucius (551–479  BC )."]}]},{"name":"Roberto","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Germanic.  See  <b>Robert</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Conte Roberto di Medania was born in 1098, in Naples, Naples, Campania, Italy, his father, Goffredo Di Medania, was 28 and his mother, Sichelgaita di Salerno, was 36. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Giuditta di Buonalbergo. He died about 1160, in his hometown, at the age of 63."},"et":{"1098–circa 1160":"1098–umbes 1160","1098–1160":"1098–1160","1097–1160":"1097–1160","1100–Female":"1100–Surnud","1124–Male":"1124–Surnud","1125